  "prompt": "What are common early pregnancy symptoms or signs that make you feel you may be pregnant?",
  "response": "Early pregnancy symptoms can vary from person to person, but some common signs that might indicate you are pregnant include:\n\n1. **Missed Period**: One of the earliest and most reliable signs of pregnancy is a missed menstrual cycle.\n\n2. **Nausea or Morning Sickness**: Feeling nauseous, often in the morning, but it can occur at any time of the day.\n\n3. **Tender or Swollen Breasts**: Hormonal changes can cause breast tenderness or swelling in early pregnancy.\n\n4. **Fatigue**: Increased levels of progesterone can make you feel unusually tired.\n\n5. **Frequent Urination**: Early in pregnancy, hormonal changes can lead to increased urination.\n\n6. **Food Aversions or Cravings**: You may develop a sudden dislike for certain foods or crave foods you don't usually eat.\n\n7. **Mood Swings**: Hormonal changes in pregnancy can cause emotional fluctuations.\n\n8. **Light Spotting or Implantation Bleeding**: Some women experience light spotting when the fertilized egg attaches to the uterine lining.\n\n9. **Constipation**: Hormonal changes can slow down the digestive system, leading to constipation.\n\n10. **Bloating**: Hormonal changes can also cause bloating, similar to what you might experience before a period.\n\n11. **Headaches**: Changes in hormone levels can trigger headaches in some women.\n\n12. **Dizziness or Lightheadedness**: Pregnant women may feel dizzy or lightheaded due to hormonal changes and shifts in blood pressure.\n\nIf you suspect you might be pregnant based on these symptoms, it's a good idea to take a home pregnancy test and consult with a healthcare professional for confirmation and advice.",
